European Coal Derivatives Fall 0.6% for Second Straight Retreat

-- B y   A l i s t a i r   H o l l o w a y
-- 
2011-03-25T09:05:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-25/european-coal-derivatives-fall-0-6-for-second-straight-retreat.html
Benchmark European coal derivatives
had a second consecutive retreat.  Coal for delivery to Amsterdam, Rotterdam or Antwerp with
settlement next year fell 75 cents, or 0.6 percent, to $130 a
metric ton by 8:58 a.m. in  London .  The data are drawn from information supplied by ICAP Plc,
 GFI Group Inc. (GFIG) , Spectron Group Ltd., Credit Suisse Group AG, IHS
McCloskey, Bloomberg, Tradition Financial Services and Tullett
Prebon Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alistair Holloway in London at 
 aholloway1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter@bloomberg.net . 